############################

DvDre,
a set of bash scripts to aid in DVD rip/encode with an added nfo, html, info file,
that contains metadata and IMDb film info and thumbnails. [ If Available ]
the script's (tools)
DvDre – The Shell Script Wrapper to the Following Scripts
VidRip – DVD rip to harddisk
VidEnc – DVD or File Encode with x264
AudioRip – DVD Audio Ripper Copy|or AAC Conversion
SubRip – Subtitle Ripper
MuxIt – Mux Video, Audio, Subtitles to MKV or MP4
- -
MI nfo Create – Create MetaData NFO & HTML Files using iMBD Dump & iMBD ThumbGrab
iMDB Dump – Dump IMDb Film Info to the Shell [If Available]
iMDB ThumbGrab – Grab IMDb Film ThumbNails [If Available]

 The is all still very much in process of being written and tested. 
  It's an idea based off others works.
 I'm trying to do some of what I've seen and more.
  With time maybe this will be a decent set of tools to backup your video files w/proper information
if available.

Date:
Tue Aug 25 20:07:07 PDT 2009

I'm pretty lazy and very much still learning, and using this to 
 teach myself some decent bash programming.

 .... M. reDD

